This paper is about reinforcement learning algorithms for continuous control tasks, which are typically studied in the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also focuses on the use of autoregressive policies for exploration, which is relevant to the sub-field of robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper includes empirical results on real-world robotic hardware, which suggests a potential connection to computer vision (cs.CV) as well.
